                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851R.00/120: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom (<persName type="from"
                            >Matthews</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-25T02:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 25, 1942—2 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 24—10:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7347. Radio Algiers has just announced that Admiral Darlan was attacked and
                    subsequently died this afternoon and that his assassin was caught and is being
                    questioned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
